Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In #Oven-Ready Aluminum Tray{}, combine @Arborio Rice{3/4%cup}, @Diced Salami{2%ounce}, @Veggie Stock Concentrates{2%unit}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1%unit}, and @water{1 3/4%cups}. (For 4 servings, divide everything between two trays, using 1 3⁄4 cups water for each tray.)

Cover tray tightly with #foil{}. Bake on middle rack until rice is cooked, ~{30-35%minutes} (for 4, bake two trays side by side on middle rack).

Meanwhile, place @Spinach{5%ounce} in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Cut 2 TBSP butter (4 TBSP for 4 servings) into small pieces. Quarter @Lemon{1}.

Once rice is done, carefully remove foil (watch out for steam!); stir in spinach, @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{1%ounce}, and butter pieces until combined (for 4, divide everything between two trays). TIP: If risotto seems too thick, add a splash of water.

Taste and season with @?Pepper{} if desired.

Divide risotto between shallow bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan Cheese{6%tablespoon} and as many @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> Imagine rich, creamy risotto made easy in the oven! You'll combine arborio rice and salty bites of salami right in the oven-ready tray (no pans to clean!). When it comes out of the oven, stir in spinach, tangy sun-dried tomato paste, and a swirl of butter for all the feels! Finish with a sprinkle of Parm, chili flakes, and lemon.